---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About OperatorStack"
  description="OperatorStack is built by a team of multi-location operators who have collectively managed thousands of venues. Real reviews from real deployments."
>

  <div style="background:var(--gray-50); border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200); padding:4rem 1.5rem 3rem;">
    <div style="max-width:680px; margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="tag tag-navy" style="margin-bottom:1rem; display:inline-block;">About</span>
      <h1>Built by Operators. For Operators.</h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.15rem; color:var(--gray-600); margin-top:1rem;">
        Most software review sites are run by marketers who have never managed a second location, handled multi-site payroll, or watched a CRM break at scale. OperatorStack is different.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="content-width">
      <div class="prose">

        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <p>OperatorStack is built by a team of multi-location operators who have collectively managed thousands of business locations across restaurants, gyms, salons, retail stores, and service businesses.</p>

        <p>We have evaluated thousands of software tools over our careers — not from free trials or press kits, but from real deployments with real money on the line. When we review a CRM, we are evaluating it for someone managing dozens of locations with automated billing, not a solopreneur with 10 clients.</p>

        <p>That operational experience is what makes OperatorStack different from every other review site.</p>

        <h2>Why We Built This Site</h2>
        <p>Every time we needed to evaluate a software tool for our businesses, we found the same useless content: generic feature listicles, affiliate sites with "reviews" written from 14-day free trials, and articles clearly written for marketers — not operators.</p>

        <p>There was no resource that answered the questions operators actually ask: How does this CRM handle thousands of locations? What breaks when you scale? How do these tools connect to each other in a real operational stack?</p>

        <p>OperatorStack fills that gap.</p>

        <h2>Our Standards</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No sponsored placements</strong> — rankings are never for sale</li>
          <li><strong>No free trial reviews</strong> — every tool has been deployed in real businesses</li>
          <li><strong>No sugarcoating</strong> — if a tool has problems, we say so</li>
          <li><strong>Full cost transparency</strong> — real pricing at scale, including hidden costs</li>
          <li><strong>Updated quarterly</strong> — software changes, and our reviews change with it</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <p>This site earns revenue through affiliate links. When you sign up for a tool through an OperatorStack link, we earn a commission — at no cost to you. This is how the site stays free and independent.</p>

        <p>We disclose every affiliate relationship explicitly. We never inflate ratings for a commission. If a tool has a real flaw, we say so. That honesty is the only thing that makes this site worth reading.</p>

        <p><a href="/affiliate-disclaimer">Read our full affiliate disclosure policy →</a></p>

        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>CRM &amp; sales tools</strong> — with a focus on multi-location and multi-user scenarios</li>
          <li><strong>Email marketing platforms</strong> — for operators building partner or customer lists</li>
          <li><strong>Automation tools</strong> — Zapier, GoHighLevel workflows, onboarding systems</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting &amp; web performance</strong> — for operators running business websites</li>
          <li><strong>Scheduling &amp; payroll</strong> — multi-location employee management</li>
          <li><strong>POS &amp; payment processing</strong> — restaurant, retail, and service POS systems</li>
          <li><strong>Billing &amp; financial tools</strong> — invoicing, accounting, partner payouts</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout callout-teal" style="margin-top:2rem;">
          <strong>Get the Free Operator's Toolkit</strong>
          12 tools stack-ranked for multi-location operators — with exact pricing and what each replaces. <a href="/operator-toolkit">Download free →</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>
